    "Let us consider the scenario where region L is polarized in valley K, and locally has Chern number C = +1.",
    "For region R, we have two options for the local valley polarization:(1) The valley switches across the DW, such that region R is polarized in valley K ′ and has Chern number C = +1.",
    "We dub this the valley wall.",
    "Since the Chern numbers C L = C R are unchanged, the gapless chiral edge modes of the two domains are counter-propagating and carry opposite valley character.",
    "If intervalley hybridization occurs 71, then these edge modes can gap each other out."
  ],
